Before writing any code: create the branch, then immediately open a draft PR referencing the issue(s).
Develop commit by commit on that branch — small, focused commits with conventional messages.
Keep the PR description and linked issues updated as work progresses.
Mark the PR ready for review when the task is complete. After completing tasks, create a subagent, and review it via fresh context. Update the pr with the review, and implement patches if needed with commits.
Use the GitHub MCP for all of this.

Use context7 mcp for the docuement retrival. You can use project skills for the certain tasks.
